sources.title: In Old Caliente (1939)
sources.description: Roy works for rancher Don Jose Vargas. When his son Carlos is robbed of the cattle drive money Roy is framed for it. Also there is a romantic interest for Roy by Carlos's daughter Rita and Gabby's niece Jean. Mystic Nights Videos

sources.title: In Old Caliente (1939) ROY ROGERS
sources.description:
Stars: Roy Rogers, Lynne Roberts, George 'Gabby' Hayes
Director: Joseph Kane

Americans come west to California in the hope of peaceful settlement. Roy and Gabby sing a duet: "We're Not Coming Out Tonight." Other songs include "Sundown on the Rangeland" and "Ride on Vaquero."

metadata.Plot: Don Jose's foreman Sujarto is an informer for an outlaw gang. After Don Jose's son Carlos is robbed, Roy and Gabby find the outlaws but end up captured and blamed for the robbery. They get even deeper into trouble when Sujarto kills Don Jose and blames Roy. They are able to escape and Roy convinces Carlos that Sujarto killed his father. Roy then has a plan that will bring Sujarto and the gang into the open.
metadata.Actors: Roy Rogers, Lynne Roberts, George 'Gabby' Hayes
